                                 Combat

     Combat, one of the most popular activities on a mud has just a few
rules to live by.  Most importantly, you must be properly equipped.  Also,
you must watch your damage.
     Proper equipment is a must in combat.  For beginners, there is Erga's
equipment shop with free equipment (n, w, w, s from here).  It's not the
best around, but it's a good start.  If you've got a bit of money to spend
there is an an armory west just inside the city near the north exit.  Also,
there's of course the main shop e, s, s, w from the west exit of town.
     Once you've gotten your gear together, remember to wear and wield
everything, or just type equip to get it all worn and wielded at once.
     After preparation, and you've found you're victim and begun your
attack, watch the damage done.  The best ways of doing this are by typing
. or mon.  . gives you a quick show of your health.  Mon shows it to you
as it changes.
     Most all of your stats affect your performance in combat so make
sure to keep them well balanced.  And be careful.  Most of all, have fun.
Oh, one last thing: Every once in a while despite careful preparation the
angel of death comes for you.  When dead, make your way to the church in
town and type pray to come back to life minus a bit of your power.
